! Penny (1d) - the basic silver coin
! Groat (4d) - introduced 1279, silver
! Half-groat (2d) - silver
! Farthing (¼d) - small silver piece, or literally a penny cut into quarters
! Halfpenny (½d) - small silver piece, or a penny cut in half

! for chests: small cup, needle & thread



! both medicines & poisons for medicine cabinet:

! Hemlock (Conium maculatum):

! Used externally for pain relief, tumors, skin conditions
! Distinctive mousy/musty smell
! Causes paralysis, respiratory failure
! Famous from Socrates

! Henbane (Hyoscyamus niger):

! Sedative, pain relief, used in sleeping draughts
! Bitter, unpleasant smell
! Causes delirium, hallucinations, death at high doses
! Part of medieval "spongia somnifera" (surgical anesthesia)

! Monkshood/Wolfsbane (Aconitum):

! Pain relief externally, fever reducer
! No strong smell (harder for detection)
! Fast-acting heart failure
! Extremely deadly even in small amounts

! Deadly Nightshade/Belladonna (Atropa belladonna):

! Dilates pupils, treats muscle spasms, used in small doses
! Berries or tincture
! Causes dry mouth, delirium, death
! Sweet-tasting (could be hidden in food/drink)

! Foxglove (Digitalis):

! Heart conditions, dropsy (edema)
! No distinctive smell
! Causes heart arrhythmia, death
! Dosage is tricky even for legitimate use


! Aldwin



! Vigil (eighth hour of night: 2 a.m.)
! Matins (a later portion of Vigil, from 3 a.m. to dawn)
! Lauds (dawn; approximately 5 a.m., but varies seasonally)
! Prime (early morning, the first hour of daylight, approximately 6 a.m.)
! Terce (third hour, 9 a.m.)
! Sext (sixth hour, noon)
! None (ninth hour, 3 p.m.)
! Vespers (sunset, approximately 6 p.m.)
! Compline (end of the day before retiring, approximately 7 p.m.)

! game starts at lauds, ends at compline?
